description:
Update ChatAdapter API: typed becomes primary, untyped gets suffix. NO deprecation - just clean rename.

Location: crates/dspy-rs/src/adapter/chat.rs and adapter/mod.rs

Renames:
- `format_user_message_typed` → `format_user_message<S>` (typed is now PRIMARY)
- `format_system_message_typed` → `format_system_message<S>`
- `format_user_message` (old untyped) → `format_user_message_untyped`
- `format_system_message` (old untyped) → `format_system_message_untyped`

Signature changes:
```rust
// Typed (PRIMARY) - now returns Result
pub fn format_system_message<S: Signature>(&self) -> Result<String, RenderError>;
pub fn format_user_message<S: Signature>(&self, input: &S::Input) -> Result<String, RenderError>;

// Untyped (legacy, for MetaSignature + Example) - keeps returning String
pub fn format_system_message_untyped(&self) -> String;
pub fn format_user_message_untyped(&self, input: &Example) -> String;
```

Call site migration (hard break, no deprecation):
```rust
// Before
let msg = adapter.format_user_message_typed::<MySig>(&input);

// After
let msg = adapter.format_user_message::<MySig>(&input)?;
```

Acceptance Criteria:
1. format_user_message_typed renamed to format_user_message (generic)
2. Old untyped format_user_message renamed to format_user_message_untyped
3. Same for system message variants
4. Typed methods return Result<String, RenderError>
5. All call sites updated
6. NO deprecation warnings - clean break
7. cargo check passes
